710127f-a.title: Manhattan: 8th Avenue - 25th Street (West)
710127f-a.text:
306-314 Eight Avenue, east side, between W 25th and 26th
Streets, showing Miner's Theatre. This structure, originally
built in 1881, was rebuilt in 1904 after a fire the preceeding
year. In 1913 it closed, to be later reopened as the Chelsea
(Movie Theatre).
